cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper deals with the security and privacy implications of using decentralized systems such as distributed ledgers and IPFS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the decentralized computing capabilities of Ethereum, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of IPFS also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the illegal activities that can be carried out using these technologies, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
